    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's just that \"asking for a hand\" feels like just more work. more pretending. like if i keep trying to mend these pieces, i'm just wasting time on something that was never meant to be whole again. sometimes the most \"honest\" thing isn't asking for help, it's just accepting that the story is over. it feels like there's a certain kind of peace in just... letting go of the struggle to be \"okay.\"",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
